description: Xtu initialization failed. See sheXdslLineInitializationResult for potential reasons.
This parameter indicates whether the last full initialization procedure was successful. If the last
initialization procedure was not successful, this parameter provides the reason. It is coded as an
integer in the 0 to 5 range coded as follows:
This error occurs with inconsistencies in configuration parameters. E.g., when the line is
initialized in an xDSL Transmission system where an xTU does not support the configured
Maximum Delay or the configured Minimum or Maximum Data Rate for one or more
2 -> Configuration not feasible on the line
This error occurs if the Minimum Data Rate cannot be reached on the line with the
Minimum Noise Margin, Maximum PSD level, Maximum Delay and Maximum Bit Error
Ratio for one or more bearer channels.
This error occurs, for example, due to corrupted messages or bad syntax messages or if no
common mode can be selected in the G.994.1 handshaking procedure or due to a timeout.
This error occurs if the peer xTU is not powered or not connected or if the line is too long
to allow detection of a peer xTU.
5 -> Any other or unknown Initialization Failure cause.
6 -> G.998.4 Retransmission mode was not selected while retransmission mode = rtxForced

loop test was startet by operator or on remote request.
The status of the recent occasion the Loop diagnostics mode
forced (LDSF) was issued for the associated line. Possible
none (1) - The default value in case LDSF was never
inProgress (3) - The Loop Diagnostics process is in
unsupported (4) - The NE or the line card doesn't support
cannotRun (5) - The NE cannot initiate the command, due
aborted (6) - The Loop Diagnostics process aborted.
failed (7) - The Loop Diagnostics process failed.
illegalMode (8) - The NE cannot initiate the command, due
to the specific mode of the relevant
adminUp (9) - The NE cannot initiate the command, as
noResources (11)- The NE cannot initiate the command, due
to lack of internal memory resources.

variables.name: SHE-XDSL-MIB::sheXdslLineRunningApsProfileVector

description: xDSL line status event notification indicating that the status of the active configuration of
one or more xDSL lines indicated by sheXdslLineStatusActConfProfile has changed.
This trap can be sent as a collected trap, which means that this notification could contain
more than one sheXdslLineStatusActConfProfile variable binding.
In certain circumstances it is possible that more than a single line may be impacted
by fallback and to avoid sending many individual traps for each affected line, the line
objects are collected in this single trap for each affected card.
Thus, it is possible that only one notification per card is sent containing
the sheXdslLineStatusActConfProfile of all affected lines on that card.

event.Summary: XDSL line status active configuration profile changed to $v1

description: The status of the active configuration of this line, indicating which xDSL line
configuration is currently applied to this line.
This status can be used to determe whether the line is currently in fallback mode.
the individual profile assignments on the line reference the actual xDSL line
sheXdslLineConfProfileVector references the xDSL line configuration vector in use;
sheXdslLineRunningApsProfileVector references the xDSL line configuration vector in use;
sheXdslLineFallbackConfProfileVector references the xDSL line configuration vector in use.
Fallback is only supported on IU cards that support vectoring. On all other cards
the used xDSL line configuration vector is always individualProfilesOrConfProfileVector(0).

modified also and change his bridgePortMode to 'useAtmoE'.

Maximum Delay or the configured Minimum or Maximum Data Rate for one or more
2 -> Configuration not feasible on the line

Minimum Noise Margin, Maximum PSD level, Maximum Delay and Maximum Bit Error

description: Customer can select a single mode or enable more then one possible standard
and the system will select the mode depending on the detected remote side.
At minimum, one bit has always to be set!
The configurator has to check, that only compatible modes are selected at the same time.
This has also to be checked during line assignment.
This parameter cannot be directly configured. The NE will always set the corresponding bits
depending on the valid configuration of ModeSpecificPSDProfilesUsed parameter. The reason for
this implementation is the precondition that the number of valid ModeSpecificPSDProfile pointers
must correspond exactly to the xDSL modes enabled in sheXdsl2LineSpectrumConfProfXtuTransSysEna.

description: This alarm indicates that an automatic port reset to solve transmission
problems has not been successful for the given xDSL line and the system
is attempting to recover the port through further resets.
This is only possible if the feature Automatic Port Reset is enabled
When Automatic Port Reset is enabled and a port leaves SHOWTIME,
because of transmission problems (LOS, LPR, etc.), an immediate port reset
will be carried out. If the port does not reach SHOWTIME after a further
time period as determined by the vendor (non-configurable), another reset
will be triggered and this alarm will be raised for the port.
The alarm will be cleared, if the port subsequently reaches SHOWTIME or
the port's admin state is set to 'locked', causing the port's counter
of reset events back to zero.

Summary.eval: ($v4==5) ? 'Automatic port reset failure on XDSL line cleared' : 'Automatic port reset failed on XDSL line'

description: The value of one or more instances of sheXdslXLineVectoringStatusErrorStateXtuc and/or
This trap can be sent as a collected trap, which means that this notification could contain
more than one set of the following indexed objects: sheXdslXLineVectoringStatusErrorStateXtuc,
In certain circumstances it is possible that more than a single line may be impacted
by line vectoring errors and to avoid sending many individual traps for each affected line,
the relevant line status objects are collected in this single trap for each affected card.
Thus, it is possible that only one notification per card is sent containing
sheXdslXLineVectoringStatusErrorStateXtur for all affected lines on that card.

Summary.eval: ($v1==1 && $v2==1) ? 'XDSL line vectoring error on both xtuc and xtur' : (($v1==1) ? 'XDSL line vectoring error on xtuc' : (($v2==1) ? 'XDSL line vectoring error on xtur' : 'XDSL line vectoring errors cleared'))

description: Reports the state of the line in the downstream direction (xtuc side).
It is a bit-map of possible conditions.
noDefect(0) - There are no defects on the line.
lossOfFraming(1) - xtu failure due to not receiving a valid frame.
lossOfSignal(2) - xtu failure due to not receiving signal.
lossOfPower(3) - xtu failure due to loss of power.
lossOfSignalQuality(4) - Loss of Signal Quality is declared when the Noise Margin
falls below the Minimum Noise Margin, or the bit-error-rate
lossOfLink(5) - xtu failure due to inability to link with peer xtu. Set
whenever the transceiver is in the 'Warm Start' state.
variables.name: SHE-XDSL-MIB::sheXdslXLineAutoPortResetEventLogXtucStatus

description: Reports the state of the line in the upstream direction (xtur side).
It is a bit-map of possible conditions.
noDefect(0) - There are no defects on the line.
lossOfFraming(1) - xtu failure due to not receiving a valid frame.
lossOfSignal(2) - xtu failure due to not receiving signal.
lossOfPower(3) - xtu failure due to loss of power.
lossOfSignalQuality(4) - Loss of Signal Quality is declared when the Noise Margin
falls below the Minimum Noise Margin, or the bit-error-rate
lossOfLink(5) - xtu failure due to inability to link with peer xtu. Set
whenever the transceiver is in the 'Warm Start' state.
variables.name: SHE-XDSL-MIB::sheXdslXLineAutoPortResetEventLogXturStatus

description: Reports the last successful transmitted initialization state in the
downstream direction (xtuc side) at the last full initialization
Initialization states are defined in the individual xDSL Recommendations
and are counted beginning 0, if G.994.1 is used, and 1, if not used, up to
showtime. This parameter must be interpreted along with the xDSL Transmission
0..11 - States values are identical for central office (xtuc) and remote side (xtur).
12..32 - State values have different meanings at the central office and remote sides.
255 - (notAvailable(255)) Information is not available on IU.
variables.name: SHE-XDSL-MIB::sheXdslXLineAutoPortResetEventLogXtucLastStateTransmitted

description: The method to be used to detect a single wire interruption on the associated line(s).
attenuationBased(1) - an interruption of the line will be detected using
attenuation measured on the line only.
attenuationAndMeltBased(2) - an interruption of the line will be detected using
attenuation measured on the line and other MELT
variables.name: SHE-XDSL-MIB::sheXdslXLineInterruptionDetectionProfileDetectionMethod

description: The required behavior of the feature when a single wire interruption is detected
doNothing(0) - if an interruption is detected, no action will be
taken; only the counters will be incremented.
forceLineDown(1) - if an interruption is detected, the operational
state of the line will be forced into the down state.
forceFallback(2) - if an interruption is detected, the line will be
forced into using the fallback line config vector.
variables.name: SHE-XDSL-MIB::sheXdslXLineInterruptionDetectionProfileDetectionBehavior

description: The required behavior for allowing a line a retry at initialization following detection of a
noRetry(1) - no retry will be performed
fixedWaitingPeriod(2) - a retry at initialization of the line will be allowed
after a fixed configured waiting period.
exponentialBackoff(3) - the exponential backoff algorithm will be applied
to determine when a retry will be allowed.
variables.name: SHE-XDSL-MIB::sheXdslXLineInterruptionDetectionProfileRetryBehavior

detection of a single wire interruption on that line.
0 - no limitation on the number of retries allowed.

description: This object enables/disables the Automatic Port Reset feature for all
xDSL lines on all IU cards supporting this feature on the NE.
When Automatic Port Reset is enabled and a port leaves SHOWTIME,
because of transmission problems (LOS, LPR, etc.), an immediate port reset
will be carried out. If the port does not reach SHOWTIME after a further
time period as determined by the vendor (non-configurable), another reset
will be triggered, in which case a sheXdslXLineAutoPortResetAlarm will be
The alarm will be cleared, if the port subsequently reaches SHOWTIME or
the port's admin state is set to 'locked', causing the port's counter
of reset events back to zero.

description: Path name for the compressed archive file containing the reported XLIN data on the server referenced by
This path should be set relative to the server root and use only linux notation ( / ).
Spaces in path names are not allowed, because of possible problems with
different file transfer protocol implementations (client and/or server)!
Depending on the server configuration, a leading / in the path configuration could
force a write or read action outside of the root directory of the used user account.
In this case, the path is not longer relative to the root. It will be read as
variables.name: SHE-XDSL-MIB::sheXdslDiagnosticFextCouplingXlinDataFilePathName

description: Optional prefix to be used when generating the file name stem of the data file and the compressed
archive file containing the reported XLIN data to be transfered to the server referenced by
The file is a tar gzip archive that includes the raw data of the measurement in a .csv
The generated file name stems contains additional information about the NE, the
vectored system measured and the date and time of the measurement as follows.
variables.name: SHE-XDSL-MIB::sheXdslDiagnosticFextCouplingXlinDataFileNamePrefix
